d to show the world who she is instead of coloring her body with random images and needing thirty expressions to show her soul.', 2338, 0), (95343, 'Gratitude is a soul blooming profusely!', 19475, 0), (95344, 'My soul is the gods’; my heart is yours.Leiard smiled—a sly, secretive smile. It was an expression she had never seen him wear before. Was this just her mind embellishing the mood she sensed from him? I’ve always suspected souls were a concept the gods invented to encourage people to serve them. In fact, I once had a conversation with a god in which he admitted that —', 905, 0), (95345, 'It is not when a man is at the end of his life, but when a man is at the end of his profession, that his soul shows itself.', 3789, 0), (95346, 'The living WORD, medicine for the soul.', 2878, 0), (95347, 'Becoming thoughtless does not mean, non-existence of thought. It simply means reaching out to the absolute state of the consciousness which is free of thinking. All of us need a thought to allow universal consciousness to express itself through finite medium – but in the end – the expression itself is infinite, whether visible or invisible', 19476, 0), (95348, 'A happy healthy soul', 19477, 0), (95349, 'The spirit of life, the divinity of the soul.', 2878, 0), (95350, 'Act on your instinct. It is the spirit of your divinity.', 2878, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (95351, 'May your spirit be empower divine power.', 2878, 0), (95352, 'For even if we have the sensation of being always surrounded by our own soul, it is not as though by a motionless prison: rather, we are in some sense borne along with it in a perpetual leap to go beyond it.', 450, 0), (95353, 'I became lost in a world darkened beyond any known shade of black, and the only light that I have seen since...is you.', 16565, 0), (95354, 'If you want to be successful in any area of life, you have to work on developing your soul.', 3800, 0), (95355, 'Peace is the nature of the mind. And bliss is the nature of the Soul!', 6286, 0), (95356, 'Study the nature around you, but also within you.', 5117, 0), (95357, 'May your soul be sparked by the glorious light.', 2878, 0), (95358, 'My soul is filled with exceedingly joy.', 2878, 0), (95359, 'It is a curious thing, Harry, but perhaps those who are best suited to power are those who have never sought it. Those who, like you, have leadership thrust upon them, and take up the mantle because they must, and find to their own surprise that they wear it well.', 28, 0), (95360, 'To handle yourself, use your head; to handle others, use your heart.', 141, 0), (95361, 'The mediocre teacher tells. The good teacher explains. The superior teacher demonstrates. The great teacher inspires.', 1820, 0), (95362, 'Our chief want is someone who will inspire us to be what we know we could be.', 760, 0), (95363, 'Don''t follow the crowd, let the crowd follow you.', 1945, 0), (95364, 'The greatest leader is not necessarily the one who does the greatest things. He is the one that gets the people to do the greatest things.', 1727, 0), (95365, 'Leadership is not about titles, positions or flowcharts. It is about one life influencing another.', 1810, 0), (95366, 'You have to be burning with an idea, or a problem, or a wrong that you want to right. If you''re not passionate enough from the start, you''ll never stick it out.', 1064, 0), (95367, 'If your actions create a legacy that inspires others to dream more, learn more, do more and become more, then, you are an excellent leader.', 1300, 0), (95368, 'Don’t waste your energy trying to educate or change opinions; go over, under, through, and opinions will change organically when you’re the boss. Or they won’t. Who cares? Do your thing, and don’t care if they like it.', 1219, 0), (95369, 'Power isn’t control at all — power is strength, and giving that strength to others. A leader isn’t someone who forces others to make him stronger; a leader is someone willing to give his strength to others that they may have the strength to stand on their own.', 763, 0), (95370, 'Only one man in a thousand is a leader of men -- the other 999 follow women.', 1040, 0), (95371, 'I have three precious things which I hold fast and prize. The first is gentleness; the second is frugality; the third is humility, which keeps me from putting myself before others. Be gentle and you can be bold; be frugal and you can be liberal; avoid putting yourself before others and you can become a leader among men.', 15, 0), (95372, 'Don''t tell people how to do things, tell them what to do and let them surprise you with their results.', 2034, 0), (95373, 'Management is doing things right', 19478, 0), (95374, 'You are good. But it is not enough just to be good. You must be good for something. You must contribute good to the world. The world must be a better place for your presence. And the good that is in you must be spread to others....', 197, 0), (95375, 'A man can only lead when others accept him as their leader, and he has only as much authority as his subjects give to him. All of the brilliant ideas in the world cannot save your kingdom if no one will listen to them.', 508, 0), (95376, 'Victory has a hundred fathers and defeat is an o', 1680, 0), (95377, 'He who cannot be a good follower cannot be a good leader.', 1116, 0), (95378, 'Leadership and learning are indispensable to each ', 1680, 0), (95379, '...A man can only stumble for so long before he either falls or stands up straight.', 508, 0), (95380, 'Lead me, follow me, or get the hell out of my way.', 2034, 0), (95381, 'Example is not the main thing in influencing others. It is the only thing.', 1006, 0), (95382, 'The mark of a great man is one who knows when to set aside the important things in order to accomplish the vital ones.', 508, 0), (95383, 'If you would convince a man that he does wrong, do right. But do not care to convince him. Men will believe what they see. Let them see.', 1049, 0), (95384, 'Leadership is the art of getting someone else to do something you want done because he wants to do it.', 2119, 0), (95385, 'A bit of adviceGiven to a young Native AmericanAt the time of his initiation:As you go the way of life,You will see a great chasm. Jump.It is not as wide as you think.', 1123, 0), (95386, 'If you''re not confused, you''re not paying attention.', 19479, 0), (95387, 'Be with a leader when he is right, stay with him when he is still right, but, leave him when he is wrong.', 1012, 0), (95388, 'The day the soldiers stop bringing you their problems is the day you stopped leading them. They have either lost confidence that you can help them or concluded that you do not care. Either case is a failure of leadership.', 1749, 0), (95389, 'You do not lead by hitting people over the head -- that''s assault, not leadership.', 2119, 0), (95390, 'The key to successful leadership is influence, not authority.', 15951, 0), (95391, 'Efficiency is doing the thing right. Effectiveness is doing the right thing.', 10835, 0), (95392, 'A leader. . .is like a shepherd. He stays behind the flock, letting the most nimble go out ahead, whereupon the others follow, not realizing that all along they are being directed from behind.', 1722, 0), (95393, 'Do you know that one of the great problems of our age is that we are governed by people who care more about